title: Larger Masks Fit Adult Males Better
text:
Review of Reusable Washable Face Mask with Adjustable Ear Loops & Nose Clip-3 Layer Mask with Built in Cotton Filter for Extra Protection- Unisex Fits Most Adults and Teens (4Pack) sold by LivingLife

The measurements listed in the product description seem to be accurate as I found these to be 8 ½ x 5 1/8 inches (22 x 13.3 cm) but please also note that the center of the mask is curved which affects the vertical (nose to chin) fit.

These masks will fit US adult males reasonably well. My head size is probably about average and these provide pretty complete coverage although I do find these masks to ride (usually up from the chin but sometimes slipping downward) when walking and/or talking. Another ¼ inch (0.6 cm) would be great.

These are listed as being 4 layers but we obviously will only see the innermost and outermost layers which are as being cotton (inner) and a polyester mesh (outer).

A great positive for adult males in the US and similar is that the masks are pretty wide. This means that the stress points where the elastic cord are closer to the ear so is more likely to lie flat or flatter against the face reducing leakage on the sides.

Mask seems to be well constructed and stitched with no loose threads.

The nose bridge seems to be wider than usual but is also thinner than usual so does not hold its shape quite as well.

The ear loops are longer than usual and the fit is adjusted by the now common rubber or nylon tube that slides along to ear loops. The elastic cord is acceptable in terms of comfort.

Something that I always do with reusable masks is to wash before wearing, just in case. I don’t want to breathe in any residual materials, dye, etc.

Listed as being three-layered with the middle layer being 100% cotton. The outer portions seem to be some sort of polyester blend but the material used is not listed.

title: Perfect sexy costume!
text:
First off, this is such a sexy/beautiful costume, I have yet to find another one that is also this cute! My 21st birthday is this October so I wanted a halloween costume themed party and fell in love with this costume! I ordered it about a month and a half early just in case I needed to send it back for sizing- good thing I did! I'll explain below.

2nd, I normally wear a womens US Medium Tshirt, size 11-13 jeans, and I'm a 36D. I originally ordered this costume in a size medium thinking to go along with my tshirt size. It came in quick shipping, and I tried it on. I mean, it did fit on my body, but it was just a little too tight for my liking. I wanted comfort for throughout my party, and I didn't love how it showed off all of my curves and flaps just a little to much. I am not "curvy" so I don't have the cute body type where a skin-tight suit is never a question. I just have love handles every 4 inches and I wasn't feeling my greatest in the medium. As previous reviews have said, and I will attest, is that this piece is advertised as "no see-through" when in fact it's a *little* see-through. Again, previous reviewers have warned about and I will attest to, the zipper can be a little tricky to get up. A trick I used was to zip it up a few inches before putting it on, and then it's easier to zip up when it's on and already zipped a few inches. Problem solved.

But I still went through the process of returning it, which I have no issue with because I've returned amazon items before. Amazon's returning process is the easiest thing I've ever dealt with. (Props to amazon!) So I went to my local UPS Store, and got my refund in a matter of a few hours. Then I proceeded to order the large. It said it was going to take about a week til delivery, it was here in 3 days. So again, I'm impressed with (and appreciate) the quick delivery. I tried on the large and I'm in LOVE! It fits so much better, comfier, doesn't suffocate my body, and accentuates my best features (though I dont have many lol). It's stretchy & pretty breathable. I just love everything about this costume. I'll detail each pro & con of the costume:

Con 1: Just fair warning, whatever t-shirt size you wear, and depending how tight you like your clothes, you might want to order a size up. The large still hugs my body but not as suffocating as the medium. The zipper came up a lot easier on the large than the medium, but I still used that few inches before putting it on method. Worked great. When I had the medium, there were plenty of stretched lines in the costume which was another reason I decided to order a size up. The large still had some lines showing but it's not anything that would ruin the look of the costume.

Con 2: The headband is pretty weighted, so I might have to use bobbi pins or something to hold it in place. (I'm just wearing it on my own hair, not a wig like some others have done.) But honestly this headband is SO cute, and I've got a solution for the weight. So is it really that much of a "con"? Don't think so.

Pro 1: this is seriously the cutest halloween costume I have ever seen. The pink fluff on the front is SO soft, and the tail is so adorable. The headband just completes the costume and I love it!

Pro 2: it was seriously fast shipping. Both times. Maybe it's just where I live vs where they're based out of (which I dont know off the top of my head) but both times the costume beat the predicted delivery dates. Fast delivery, 'nuff said.

Pro 3: If you take into consideration the reviews telling you how to choose your size, it's just an amazing costume hands down. It's not super off-sizing, which to me is a rare thing. So I was happy to find this size a better suitor for me.

Pro 4: Ladies, get yourself some gold high heels if you can wear them! The gold bottoms on the legs look FIRE with high heels. Ugh this costume is just so sexy!

Sorry for writing a NOVEL in this review, I just wanted to clearly explain sizing for future buyers, and tell them just how happy this costume makes me. Happy Halloween or whatever the occasion it is that you're wearing a costume!

Update: I wore it for my party and OMG it was comfy the entire night! The party lasted about 8 hours, and I stayed in this costume the entire time. Got so many compliments on it!

text: I purchased this with low expectations. The price was reasonable enough that I figured it was worth the gamble. I normally wear a 32DD/34D. I purchased size C on purpose.  The biggest problem I have with my implants is the gap between them.  I have a wide breast bone and cannot achieve that close cleavage look with ANY bra I have ever tried. Never ever ever. My boobs are big enough, it's just the bra never pulls them close enough horizontally to get that look. All bras mostly focus on pushing up, not so much in. So I bought this a cup smaller on purpose. I really wanted it to be tugging 'the girls' inward before I even tied the laces. Mission accomplished! This bra is amazing at getting that cleavage I always wanted.  I had no problem with the adhesive like others complain.  I was very careful to place it on clean dry skin.  I even repositioned it a couple times before I really pushed down on it from all angles to ensure a good grip. Now, I live in Phoenix, AZ so it's literally hot as heck here. I was outside for a good amount of time while wearing this.  It didn't budge.  I noticed the very edge felt like it was slightly lifting, but it never did. It stayed  put all day long. title: Cute sweater, but best suited to someone with hips well under 38" for the same baggy look
text:
I love big comfy loose sweaters, it's totally been my thing this year, and I thought this top looked so cute when I saw it. Unfortunately I will not get to wear it though, as it is too small for me. At 5'3" 130lbs I checked the size chart and the length, bust, and sleeve measurements were appropriate, so I was sure it would fit, it's big and baggy anyway. Where the bottom of the sweater falls on the hips of the model looks cute, loose and comfortable. But it will just not work for women with big hips, unfortunately. I am petite, but I have big hips, so it is very tight at the bottom, making the middle kind of just bulge over the tight part. Not a cute look, and not comfortable for me to wear. I wish there was hip measurements or a width measurement listed. My hips are about 38", and when I measured the top for this review it was 19" across, so about 38" around. So if your hips/top of your buttock areas is smaller than 38", it should be fine for you. I gave this top to my boyfriend's mom who is smaller than me, and she liked it.

I thought the sweater was a bit thinner than I expected, isn't a totally bad thing since I get warm easily, and it doesn't get too cold in Southern California anyway. The material is softish and comfortable to wear, but is not "knitted" and didn't exactly look like the photo for me, as it was a little shiny or something (see my pics), kinda weird. The sleeve cuff looks a little shorter to me too, but that isn't a big deal. There is no tag in the sweater, and it appears that you can wear it either way, both sides are the same front and back. I actually like that there is no tag, as someone with very sensitive skin related to fibromyalgia, tags can be a nuisance. The shipping time was pretty good, I ordered the top on 12/28/15, and it said it would not arrive until between 1/22/16 and 3/9/16, but I got it 1/9/16.

The bottom line is this is a cute comfortable top, but the part falling on your hips is small, so it would be best suited for someone with hips well under 38" for the same baggy look. I received this item at a discount for review purposes, but this in no way changes my opinion of the product.

title: Comfortable socks with festive holiday designs. Thin padding on soles and arch area of socks.
text:
These Christmas Holiday Socks are made up of 80% Cotton, 17% Polyester, and 3% Elastane.
None of the threads were loose on the outside of the sock or the inside of the sock.

I love the bright colors, and festive designs - perfect for this upcoming holidays!
One pair of socks is green and red, with the design of a Christmas tree.
One pair is predominantly red, with a Santa picture near the top end of the sock.
One pair is multi-colored, with the words "Merry Christmas" at the top end of the sock.

I wear size 8-1/2 men's size shoes.
These socks fit well on my feet, without bunching under the arch or at the toes after I've walked in them for a few hours around the house at night.
These socks are a bit tight around my mid-calf region (I do not have muscular calves). I resolve this by lowering the socks nearer to my ankle area.
These socks do not provide as much padding on the soles of my feet as I would like while walking on our hardwood floors; but, they feel great when I am on the carpeted areas in our home.

I've worn each pair at least once nightly, in the 6 days since I received it; each has been washed and dried once. They still fit well after washing and drying.

No washing instructions were included with the product. So, I washed these socks in the same manner as I wash previous socks that I buy at the stores: I turned the socks inside out, used a mild detergent, and used the gentle cycle on the washing machine. Then, I dried the socks by hanging them on the line in our backyard (helps to prolong the life of the socks, as opposed to putting them in the dryer).

Overall, good functional socks with eye-pleasing holiday designs.

title: Waterproof; good sensitivity to apps on my mobile devices
text:
[[VIDEOID:6d1f3a71953f430c9a2d545c8c7f3d0b]] These Sumade running gloves (size = Large) are somewhat stiff in the palm region; but, I get good dexterity at the fingertips (to get car keys out of my pockets and insert it into the ignition, or to touch the dials on my car stereo, for example).

On my 12.9" and 9.7" tablets and 5" phone, I can open up apps; I can make calls using the gloves to tap numbers on the dial pad. These gloves work so much better on all my mobile devices than the other gloves I had, thanks to touchscreen design of the fabric at the tips of the thumb, index finger, and middle finger.

However, the width of the gloves at the fingertips are too wide for me to do the finer things when I am using the two smaller mobile devices.. For instance, if I am playing a card game, it's tough for me to pick a specific card I want to use with gloves on (the fingertips of the gloves often tap the adjacent cards, rather than the card I want). So, I have to remove the gloves, and use the tips of my fingertips to choose the exact card to play.

With my 12.9" tablet, I am able to play the card games and pick out the exact card just fine while using the gloves.

These gloves do not keep my fingers as warm as some of my other, more thicker gloves. Since I have been using these gloves, temperatures in my city are about 42-50 degrees at 6-6:30 am when I leave for work.

I ran water on to my glove (tips of the gloves, palm areas, and the cuff) for over 1 minute. When I removed the glove, my hand was dry. With the outside of the glove itself wet, I was still able to open up apps on my mobile devices.

note: This large-size glove is a bit long, as the tips of my hand does not go all the way to the end of the gloves. My hand measures 7-1/2 inches from the tip of my middle finger to area where the palm meets the wrist. So, I am better off with a medium size. This is not the fault of the product; I chose the wrong size.

Overall, good waterproof property and works great on my mobile devices for most of my activities.

title: Soft, comfortable. Not binding in cuff area. Not too thick. Not enough warmth during winter.
text:
These socks are a comfortable fit for the ladies in our family, and for me (I wear a size 8 men's sneakers).

I love the decorative patterns. The stitching looks good; but, when I turned the socks inside out, there were several socks with a couple of loose threads.

The seams at the top of the toes do not bother me, but I can feel them rubbing on my toes occasionally when I wear these socks in my sneakers. They have not caused any noticeable marks on my skin at the end of the day after wearing these socks.

The cuff regions of the sock are not binding and do not cause ridge marks at my lower legs.
So far, in just the past week, after wearing 3 pairs of socks on separate days and washing and drying them twice, the socks have stayed up on my calf regions.

These socks do not provide me the warmth that I like when walking on my cold hardwood floors in the den early in the AM (with temperatures in the mid-50s), as they are not too thick. On the other hand, my feet don't sweat as much in these socks as they do in my thicker wool socks.

As I walk on our hardwood floors, the soles of my feet don't get as good of a padding as I would like. On our carpet floors, the soles of my feet feel better (as does the bottom of my feet and lower back).
Because they are not too thick, I can easily slide into my slip-on shoes.

Materials of the socks:
--- Merino wool 53%
--- Cotton 24%
--- Polyester 16%
--- Spandex 7%

Washing instruction (printed on each paper band that encloses a pair of socks; socks themselves do not have instructions imprinted in the material):
--- Machine wash warm
-- Tumble dry with low heat
--- Do not bleach

Overall, these are decent socks (thicker than the standard socks that I buy at a large mass merchandise store; but thinner than some of my wool socks that I wear during winter time) that I would enjoy using during the Fall/Spring season.

title: Heats up fairly quickly; sizing mis-match; small pockets
text:
[[VIDEOID:3e054decb92a0d1a24b7a0308eed6167]] Short summary:
This XXL-size vest fits well, but only because I wear medium-size shirts. There is a size mis-match to this vest.
Has USB-charging cable attached to one of the two pockets.
A power bank (not included) can only have a maximum width of 3-1/4 to 3-3/8, otherwise, it will not fit into the pocket. If a power bank does not fit into the pocket, then I will need to carry it in my hands while wearing the vest.

More details:

This heated vest, with USB-charging cable attached to the left pocket, is XXL-size.
I wear medium size shirts/sweaters. This vest fits me well.
note: I have family members who wear large-size shirts/sweaters. This vest is a tight fit on them.

To use this, I:

1. Attach the USB plug (which is attached to the vest) into my own power bank.

2. Press and hold down the power button (located on front of the vest, at upper-left side) for about 3 seconds.

3. The button then lights up red.
note: once button lights up red, pressing it again will get the button a white color. pressing it a 3rd time gives it a blue color. Then, it repeats (i.e. red ---> white ---> blue)

note #2: the red option gives 70-75 degrees Celsius
the white button gives 60-65 degrees Celsius
the blue button gives 40-45 degrees Celsius

4. When I am done wearing the vest, I hold down the power button, and after about 3 seconds, it turns off.

When I select the red option, I can feel the vest becoming warm in about 3-5 minutes.

The vest has two pockets. One pocket has the attached USB charging cable.
Besides the sizing, the other issue to note is that this vest has small pockets. I measure a pocket to be 4-3/4 inches deep, and 3-3/8 inches wide. I have small-size hands, and can barely fit my entire hand inside the pocket.

I have multiple power banks, of various widths. The widest width power bank that will fit inside the pocket has a width of 3-1/4 inches.

The inside of the vest is smooth to the touch.

There is a 1-page instruction manual. It includes washing instructions: can hand-wash or machine-wash; air dry; do not "kneed or beat".

I followed the wash instructions. After it was dried, I attached my power bank, and the vest worked.

Overall, this heating vest works for me - the size fits, I have power banks that fit into the pocket, and the vest heats up as expected.
